	  <concept id="i1099284"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">19.1506</ph> Women-Owned Small Business Program sole source awards.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d1254e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1268e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            A contracting officer shall consider a contract award to an EDWOSB concern on a sole source basis (see <xref href="FAR-i6_302-5.dita#i6_302-5"
                        base="i1119624"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.302-5</xref>(b)(7)) before considering small business set-asides (see <xref href="FAR-i1101696.dita#i1101696"
                        base="i1101696"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.203</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1100723.dita#i1100723"
                        base="i1100723"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  19.5</xref>) provided none of the exclusions at <xref href="FAR-i1099222.dita#i1099222"
                        base="i1099222"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.1504</xref> apply and-</p>
					          <ol id="d1254e35" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1268e39" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The acquisition is assigned a NAICS code in which SBA has determined that WOSB concerns are underrepresented in Federal procurement;</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1268e48" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The contracting officer does not have a reasonable expectation that offers would be received from two or more EDWOSB concerns; and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1268e57" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The conditions in paragraph (c) of this section exist.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1268e68" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            A contracting officer shall consider a contract award to a WOSB concern (including EDWOSB concerns) eligible under the WOSB Program on a sole source basis (see <xref href="FAR-i6_302-5.dita#i6_302-5"
                        base="i1119624"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.302-5</xref>(b)(7)) before considering small business set-asides (see <xref href="FAR-i1101696.dita#i1101696"
                        base="i1101696"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.203</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1100723.dita#i1100723"
                        base="i1100723"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  19.5</xref>) provided none of the exclusions at <xref href="FAR-i1099222.dita#i1099222"
                        base="i1099222"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.1504</xref> apply and-</p>
					          <ol id="d1254e86" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1268e90" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The acquisition is assigned a NAICS code in which SBA has determined that WOSB concerns are substantially underrepresented in Federal procurement;</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1268e99" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The contracting officer does not have a reasonable expectation that offers would be received from two or more WOSB concerns (including EDWOSB concerns); and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1268e108" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The conditions in paragraph (c) of this section exist.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1268e119" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
					          </p>
					          <ol id="d1254e125" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1268e129" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The anticipated award price of the contract, including options, will not exceed-</p>
							              <ol id="d1254e135" class="- topic/ol ">
								                <li class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d1268e139" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    $6.5 million for a requirement within the NAICS codes for manufacturing; or</p>
								                </li>
								                <li class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d1268e148" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    $4 million for a requirement within any other NAICS codes.</p>
								                </li>
							              </ol>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1268e159" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The EDWOSB concern or WOSB concern has been determined to be a responsible contractor with respect to performance.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1268e168" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The award can be made at a fair and reasonable price.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1268e179" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The SBA has the right to appeal the contracting officer’s decision not to make a sole source award to either an EDWOSB concern or WOSB concern eligible under the WOSB program.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
